label.value: actin filament of cell cortex of cell tip

definition.value: Any actin filament that is part of a cell cortex of cell tip.

label.value: mRNA binding involved in posttranscriptional gene silencing

definition.value: Any mRNA binding that is involved in posttranscriptional gene silencing.

label.value: nitrate reductase activity involved in anaerobic electron transport chain

definition.value: Any nitrate reductase activity that is involved in anaerobic electron transport chain.
A protein complex which is capable of ornithine carbamoyltransferase inhibitor activity.
A protein complex which is capable of phosphatase activity.
Any membrane that is part of an omegasome.

label.value: regulation of transcription initiation from RNA polymerase I promoter for nuclear large rRNA transcript

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription initiation from RNA polymerase I promoter for nuclear large rRNA transcript.
Catalysis of the transfer of fluoride from one side of the membrane to the other.

A protein complex which is capable of calcitonin family receptor activity. Calcitonin family receptors may form dimers, trimers or tetramers -  adrenomedullin and amylin receptors have only been observed as dimers so far.
A protein complex which is capable of amylin receptor activity.
A protein complex which is capable of translation repressor activity.
A protein complex which is capable of ATPase inhibitor activity.
Any vesicle that is part of the extracellular region.
A protein complex which is capable of glutaminase activity.

label.value: regulation of RNA polymerase III activity

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of RNA polymerase III activity.

label.value: negative regulation of RNA polymerase III activity

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of RNA polymerase III activity.

label.value: phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 5 residues involved in positive regulation of transcription elongation from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: Any phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 5 residues that is involved in positive regulation of transcription elongation from RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 2 residues involved in positive regulation of transcription elongation from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: Any phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 2 residues that is involved in positive regulation of transcription elongation from RNA polymerase II promoter.
The plus-end of a cortical microtubule.

label.value: gap junction channel activity involved in cell communication by electrical coupling

definition.value: Any gap junction channel activity that is involved in cell communication by electrical coupling.
A protein complex which is capable of sweet taste receptor activity.
A protein complex which is capable of taste receptor activity.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H+ + methylglyoxal + NADPH -lt--eq--gt- hydroxyacetone + NADP+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  IDP + H2O -eq- IMP + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  XDP + H2O -eq- XMP + phosphate.
A cytoplasmic membrane-bounded vesicle of varying size, but usually larger than 45 nm, with an electron dense granular core, found in noradrenergic and peptidergic cells.

A cytoplasmic membrane-bounded vesicle first described in dendrites, categorized by smooth membranes, electron-lucent interiors and irregular shapes. Sometimes occurs in clumps. Amorphous vesicles have been found to contain material taken up from the extracellular space, therefore suggesting that they may be part of the endosomal pathway.

A configuration of endoplasmic reticulum (ER) found in Purkinje cells in the cerebellum and in axons in the lateral vestibular nucleus, consisting of parallel and interconnecting tubules whose outer surfaces are covered by particles or ringlike structures.
A large cytoplasmic membrane-bounded vesicle with an electron dense granular core, up to 150-200 nm in diameter, found in neurosecretory cells in the hypothalamus.

Inclusion body characterized by regularly spaced sheets of tubules arranged in a whorl pattern resembling a fingerprint. Laminated bodies have been observed in neurons of the lateral geniculate nucleus.

A cytoplasmic inclusion body found in some lateral geniculate neurons and composed of sheets of tubules (25 nm in diameter) separated by dense material (about 75 nm wide), which together with the tubules whorl give a structure resembling a fingerprint.
A hexagonal array of electron dense particles attached to the cytoplasmic face of the presynaptic membrane.

Square array of closely spaced intramembrane particles, 4-6 nm in size, that form supramolecular aggregates found in the plasma membrane of astrocytes, skeletal muscle and epithelial cells. They have been shown to contain aquaporins (water channels).
A cell projection (often from glial cells such as Schwann cells) that surrounds an unmyelinated axon or cell soma.

Elongated portion of a tanycyte that sticks into the periventricular layer of neuropil where it appears to contact a blood vessel -  characterized by numerous cytoplasmic extensions. A tanycyte is a specialized elongated ventricular ependymal cell that has processes that extend to the outer, or pial, surface of the CNS.

Portion of a tanycyte that lies within the ependyma and contains the nucleus. A tanycyte is a specialized elongated ventricular ependymal cell that has processes that extend to the outer, or pial, surface of the CNS.

Elongated process of a tanycyte, devoid of cytoplasmic extensions, that courses through the hypothalamic nuclei to form small endfoot processes that terminate either on blood vessels or at the pial surface of the brain. A tanycyte is a specialized elongated ventricular ependymal cell.
Axon collateral that ramifies in the area of the soma of the cell of origin.
Part of axon of a CA3 pyramidal neuron that projects to hippocampal area CA1.

The area in the center of the anaphase spindle consisting of microtubules, microtubule bundling factors and kinesin motors where the spindle microtubules from opposite poles overlap in an antiparallel manner.
Synaptic bouton found in spinal cord on the soma and proximal dendrites of motor neurons.
Synaptic bouton found in the ventral horn of the spinal cord. F boutons range in diameter from 0.5 to 7 um and contain flattened or pleomorphic synaptic vesicles.
Synaptic expansion of hippocampal mossy fiber axon that makes contact with the thorny excrescences of hippocampal CA3 pyramidal cell dendrites.
Synaptic bouton found in the ventral horn of the spinal cord. S boutons range in diameter from 0.5 to 8 um and contain spherical synaptic vesicles.

Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by an intermediate voltage-gated channel. An intermediate voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on intermediate voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.
Ramification of basket cell axon surrounding cell bodies, forming the characteristic pericellular baskets from which the cell class derives its name.
Dense plexus formed by the descending collaterals of cerebellar basket cells that wrap around a Purkinje cell axonal initial segment.

A parallel fiber results from the bifurcation of a cerebellar granule cell axon in the molecular layer into two diametrically opposed branches, that are oriented parallel to the long axis of the folium.
The part of a dendrite where the cell projection branches, giving rise to a dendritic branch.
The center portion of a Lewy body. In Parkinson's disease, it contains a matted meshwork of filaments.
